</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[119,749,1650,1997]" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[121,186,1651,1675]" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[204,355,1650,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grande">
<emphasis box="[204,355,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">Bama grande</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[550,665,1651,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis box="[550,665,1651,1674]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in key characters, including the pale thorax and some venational features. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the armature of the mid coxa and ventral extremity of the sternopleuron, and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[627,748,1768,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis box="[627,748,1768,1792]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very reduced wing markings, the less extensive microtrichiation of the wing membrane, the longer preapical section of vein 4, and the much darker ovipositor sheath. The 
<typeStatus box="[170,216,1886,1910]" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[260,366,1885,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grande">
<emphasis box="[260,366,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. grande</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is notably larger than any available specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[268,376,1915,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis box="[268,376,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[428,568,1915,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantium">
<emphasis box="[428,568,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">B. aurantium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[119,749,1650,1997]" pageId="20" pageNumber="44">The specific epithet is a Latin adjective, indicating the relatively large size of the insect.</paragraph>
